main event: Two objects shaped like helicopters, the size of a DC-3, were observed in Eastlake, Ohio, on June 7, 1960, and disappeared over the horizon after 1.5 minutes of observation.
interesting points: The objects had one light on top and one light on the bottom., The sighting was made through binoculars., The objects disappeared moving from west to east., The report contained acknowledgments of possible explanations including balloons and aircraft., The sighting falls under the Project Blue Book documentation.
